lead_paragraph: Swimmer Yusra Mardini, who survived a harrowing sea crossing a year ago and is now among 10 refugees competing under the Olympic flag in Rio, won her preliminary heat in the 100-meter butterfly Saturday. But the result wasn't enough to advance her to the semifinals.

headline.print_headline: Syrian Refugee Swimmer Wins Heat, Won't Advance in Butterfly
